ars-technica: Google Play dumps APKs for the more Google-controlled “Android App Bundle”

Google's Android Developer Blog recaps how, starting in August, new apps being uploaded to the Play Store will need to use the new Android App Bundles (AAB) format to distribute apps. Google's solution is the Android App Bundle, which turns Android app distribution from a monolithic, universal APK into a collection of "split APKs" that can be specifically doled out by the Google Play Store for each individual device. App bundles versus the non-Google Play ecosystem

Like many new Android features, the change from APKs to Android App Bundles results in a more complex, sophisticated feature set for rolling out apps.
